?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Andy Rose</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">: Yes, I think, is the answer.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Within the HCA, we are responsible for, I think, 107,400 of those 170,000, and based on where we a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">re half</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">way through the scheme, we are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">almost exactly half</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">way towards that.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">There are schemes within that 170,000 that we are not responsible for, but certainly my understanding, both in our own delivery and wider, is that we still are on target.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q114 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">John Pugh:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> In terms of your own role, have you been involved in challenging providers about their willingness and alacrity?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Andy Rose</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">: Willingness, yes.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Ca